  "scientificVerdict": "The original Maeda deposit does not report a measured Reynolds number or complete atmospheric state; the published CFD convention remains an explicit sensitivity input. The c8, c12, and c16 measured-wing feasibility runs remain non-finite and are not quantitative bird results. Corrected stationary-sphere diagnostics isolate the first positivity loss to symmetric TRT over-relaxation. A symmetric limiter keeps c16 positive and source/force-budget closed, but the geometrically similar D=8/12/16 ladder gives an admissible negative result: sponge-excluded activation grows 3.53%, 6.65%, 8.07%, interior L2 correction remains 11.71%, 14.74%, 14.54%, and finest-two drag changes 14.81% against a 5% gate with no monotonic convergence. The D=16 radial diagnostic closes to 8.02e-7 and shows why: limiting begins within one lattice cell of the sphere, then propagates through the physical flow. At tU/D=5 only 1.11% of limiter L1 remains within 0.25D while 88.58% lies beyond 1D. A controlled D=16 bulk collision A/B then shows that second-order regularized positive BGK preserves positivity and source/force closure while reducing activation by 99.65% and relative L1 correction by 99.14%. It is nevertheless rejected because relative L2 correction is 1.0968% against the unchanged 1% gate. No boundary-only repair, flapping replay, measured-bird replay, or refinement ladder is promoted from this result."
}
